The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Calcutta, June 24: RPGs retail arm Spencers Retail is likely to enter the capital market within six months to raise funds, the companys vice-chairman Sanjiv Goenka said here today. There is no change in plan for the maiden public offer of Spencers Retail. The IPO will be in next two to four quarters of the year, Goenka said while inaugurating the first Spencers super store in the city today. 

 Kochi, June 24: Petroleum minister Murli Deora today ruled out any immediate hike in prices of petroleum products, including LPG and kerosene. Last year, the government and the oil companies had together shared 87 per cent of the under recoveries caused by the high oil prices, he said.

 New Delhi, June 24: Assocham has suggested that India should emulate the Chinese model of categorising industries for FDI regulations. It will attract more overseas investment and boost the countrys manufacturing sector, it said.

 Mumbai, June 24: The National Commodity and Derivatives Exchange (NCDEX) is looking at metal and bullion futures as a major thrust area for future growth. 

 Mumbai, June 24: Tata Chemicals, which has lined up $1 billion worth of investment over the next two to three years, will enter into bio-diesel, fresh fruits and vegetables production and distribution as part of its expansion strategy.




